    <stitle>SINGLE REDUCTION, TANDEM AXLE: INTERNATIONAL - DISASSEMBLE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>DISASSEMBLE</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="4">
            <title>INTER-AXLE DIFFERENTIAL (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1400907">Figure 7</hotlnk>)
            </title>
            <figure id="f1400907" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1400907" filename="../figg14/G1400907.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 7. Inter-Axle Assembly Components</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. BOLT</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. POWER DIVIDER CONTROL</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. RETAINER CLIP</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. AIR SHIFT CYLINDER</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. INTER-AXLE DIFFERENTIAL CASE</callout1>
                    <callout1>6. FILL PLUG</callout1>
                    <callout1>7. COVER PLATE</callout1>
                    <callout1>8. BOLT</callout1>
                    <callout1>9. BEARING CONE</callout1>
                    <callout1>10. INTER-AXLE DIFFERENTIAL GEAR</callout1>
                    <callout1>11. INTER-AXLE DIFFERENTIAL ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                    <callout1>12. LUBE RETAINER PLATE</callout1>
                    <callout1>13. DRIVE GEAR</callout1>
                    <callout1>14. NEEDLE BEARING</callout1>
                    <callout1>15. THRUST WASHER</callout1>
                    <callout1>16. CLUTCH COLLAR</callout1>
                    <callout1>17. INPUT SHAFT</callout1>
                    <callout1>18. PUMP DRIVE GEAR (OPTIONAL)</callout1>
                    <callout1>19. PINION NUT</callout1>
                    <callout1>20. INPUT YOKE</callout1>
                    <callout1>21. BOLT</callout1>
                    <callout1>22. SEAL</callout1>
                    <callout1>23. INPUT SHAFT BEARING RETAINER</callout1>
                    <callout1>24. SPACER</callout1>
                    <callout1>25. SHIM (SELECTIVE)</callout1>
                    <callout1>26. INPUT BEARING CUP</callout1>
                    <callout1>27. INPUT BEARING CONE</callout1>
                    <callout1>28. BEARING CUP</callout1>
                    <callout1>29. PLUG</callout1>
                    <callout1>30. BOLT</callout1>
                    <callout1>31. DRAIN PLUG</callout1>
                    <callout1>32. THRUST PADS</callout1>
                    <callout1>33. SHIFT FORK</callout1>
                    <callout1>34. SHIFT FORK SHAFT</callout1>
                    <callout1>35. SPRING</callout1>
                    <callout1>36. GASKET</callout1>
                    <callout1>37. WASHER</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove lube pump on models so equipped.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove intermediate case to carrier bolts. Use removal slots (
                    <hotlnk document="s14009_11.xml" xrefid="f1400905">Figure 5</hotlnk>) to separate inter-axle
                    differential assembly and intermediate case from carrier, and remove assembly.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">With intermediate case on its side, remove air shift cylinder.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove shift fork shaft, spring, and retainer clip (Items 34, 35 and 3,
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1400907">Figure 7</hotlnk>) as an assembly.
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Shift shaft threads are coated with locking compound material, so screwdriver socket and
                            ratchet should be used to remove shift shaft.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove input yoke nut.</para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Use of torque multiplier is recommended as torque specification on input nut is 900 to
                            1200 ft-lbs. (1224 to 1632 N&#8226;m). Refer to
                            <hotlnk document="s14009_43.xml" xrefid="hl1400901">SPECIAL TOOLS</hotlnk>.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove input yoke, using suitable puller (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1400908">Figure 8</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1400908" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1400908" filename="../figg14/G1400908.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 8. Removing Input Yoke</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove bolts from input shaft bearing retainer. Use removal slots shown in
                    <hotlnk document="s14009_11.xml" xrefid="f1400905">Figure 5</hotlnk>to separate bearing retainer
                    from inter-axle differential case, and remove retainer.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove input oil seal.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Press out input shaft bearing cup and shims from bearing retainer. Retain shims for
                    possible use during reassembly. Early models were not a press fit.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove input shaft assembly. Remove input yoke spacer from input shaft.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove front bearing cone from input shaft using suitable puller.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove lube pump drive gear if so equipped.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove shift fork and clutch collar.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove drive gear from inter-axle differential case.</para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Remove and discard rubber lube retainer if so equipped.</para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position intermediate case on its side. Using a soft mallet, tap on inter-axle on rear
                    differential gear that extends through the rear of intermediate case (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1400909">Figure 9</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1400909" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1400909" filename="../figg14/G1400909.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 9. Tapping on Rear Differential Gear</caption>
                </figure>
                <para>This will dislodge lube retainer, allowing removal of inter-axle differential cage and rear
                    differential gear.
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Remove and discard O-ring if so equipped.</para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove rear differential gear bearing cup from intermediate case.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove bearing cone from rear differential gear using suitable puller.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove magnetic screen (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1400910">Figure 10</hotlnk>) from intermediate case and check for abnormal
                    particles. Magnetic screen found only on models equipped with lube pump.
                </para>
                <figure id="f1400910" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1400910" filename="../figg14/G1400910.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 10. Magnetic Screen Location</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Clean and inspect all components for excessive wear, scoring or cracks. Replace damaged
                    components with original equipment replacement parts and prepare for reassembly.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <para>Inter-axle differential disassembly is complete.</para>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
